items.title: Waterskiing Santas and giant cuts of meat: Christmas around the world
items.description: From London to Bethlehem, services and festivities to mark the holiday cheer are in full swing.

items.title: Pope Leo urges 'courage' to end Ukraine war in first Christmas address
items.description: The pope also laments the condition of Palestinians during his address to worshippers at the Vatican.

items.title: Turkey arrests 115 IS suspects 'planning New Year's attacks'
items.description: Turkish authorities say firearms were seized and efforts to trace further suspected members are continuing.

items.title: Front-runner to be Bangladesh PM returns after 17 years in exile
items.description: Tarique Rahman, who has lived in London since 2008, arrives weeks before pivotal elections are held.

items.title: Trump-backed candidate wins in knife-edge Honduran election
items.description: His rival Salvador Nasralla says he will not accept the result, but urges his supporters to remain calm.
